race.comment: MONGOLIAN GOBI (3) is off a letup for this but looks well placed. His form in three starts to date has been strong, trying hard here last time out when beaten a long neck in a similar race. He can improve again into this and take plenty of beating. OBUCCI (5) will find this easier than last time at Caulfield when wide without cover on a good speed, dropping right out. The maiden win prior was good and there's been winning form out of that. Can bounce back. CASTELLITO (8) was backed into $1.40 first up at Kyneton and did enough to break her maiden, scoring by a head. Fitter for that and can measure up. BAJARIA (7) has been building nicely in three runs to date, breaking her maiden last time out having tested the smart Rohesia prior. She'll be running on. DECANTED (4) is off a let up and back to the shortest trip he's run over. That's some query but he's got ability.
